Description: Body sherd of Attic pottery skyphos(?) in Six's technique; interior black; exterior: long-legged white bird to right (tail feathers and one leg preserved); in field on left, two red dots (imitation letters); below figure tooled groove with red line below.
Curator's comments: Silhouette technique. For the bird, compare the crane on the polychrome Six's technique phiale in Rhodes (Boardman, J., Athenian Black Figure Vases. London, 1974, fig. 313).
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.23)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1253)
